IOT (Internet of things)
Internet of things (IoT) describes devices with sensors,  processing ability, software and other technologies  that connect and exchange data with other devices and systems
over the Internet or other communication networks.
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Internet_of_things

Importance of IOT:-
IoT plays a critical role in transforming businesses
By providing real-time insights into system operations, IoT empowers companies to gain a comprehensive
understanding of their processes, spanning from machine performance to supply chain and logistics operations.
https://securityjournaluk.com/why-iot-is-important/

IOT Applications:-
Smart Farming
Industrial Automation
Retail Experience
